    &lt;Title&gt;End of life care Wisdom Hospice&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Neil Relf&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I am writing on behalf of my father in law, who’s wife is currently in Wisdom Hospice in Medway Kent. It has been disclosed to us as a family that she is actively dying from cancer. 
My father in law has requested that he visit his wife of sixty years, before she passes away. This access has been denied as he has been shielding due to his age and he also has terminal cancer. 
We have been told as the hospice is part of Medway community Health Trust and this is their current protocol.
 We fail to understand if the Hospice was a charitable trust them things may be different, as we have spoken to different trusts and visiting would be allowed, even daily.  My mother in law has only days to live at the most and this tragic situation is causing so much heartache for all our family. Please help, this is desperate situation. &lt;/CommentText&gt;
